  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dc5\u0db3\u0db4\u0ddc\u0dc5 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd8\u0dad \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0d9a\u0dd0\u0db6\u0dd2\u0db1\u0da7\u0dca \u0d85\u0db1\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Cabinet approves opening of fuel market",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Cabinet approval has been granted to allow oil companies in the oil producing countries to import and sell fuel using their own funds without entering into long-term agreements with established oil companies in the country.",
        "Accordingly, oil companies will have the opportunity to import, distribute and sell fuel to Sri Lanka through long-term agreements with selected oil companies following a formal procedure.",
        "The Ceylon Petroleum Corporation contributes about 90 percent of the country's total fuel supply and the remaining 10 percent is held by the Ceylon Indian Oil Company.",
        "Commenting on this on his Twitter account, Minister Kanchana Wijesekera said that the relevant companies will be given the opportunity to open new petrol stations as well as the petrol stations currently owned by Ceypetco."
      ],
      "title_ents": [
        {
          "text": "Cabinet",
          "label": "ORG"
        }
      ],
